Exercise 1

Pokemon_dataset = clean_names(dataset)
Pokemon_dataset = Pokemon_dataset%>%
  filter(type_1 %in% c("Bug","Fire","Grass","Normal","Water","Psychic"))%>%
  mutate(type_1 = factor(type_1),legendary = factor(legendary),generation = factor(generation))

Pokemon_split = initial_split(Pokemon_dataset,prop = 0.70,strata = type_1)
Pokemon_train = training(Pokemon_split)
Pokemon_test = testing(Pokemon_split)

Pokemon_folds = vfold_cv(Pokemon_train,v=5,strata = type_1)

Pokemon_receipt = recipe(type_1 ~ legendary + generation + sp_atk + attack + speed + defense + hp + sp_def,data=Pokemon_train)%>%
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors())%>%
  step_normalize(all_predictors())

Exercise 2

We want to analyze the continuous variables we are trying to fit. It is suprising to see that all variables are positively correlated. It doesn’t make sense to me because normally for a balanced game one cannot be too strong, or strictly dominate other characters.

df <- Pokemon_train %>%
  select(sp_atk,attack,speed,defense,hp,sp_def)%>%
  drop_na()
D = cor(df)
corrplot(D,method="number")

Exercise 3

The roc_auc decreases as roc_auc increases after it reaches a maximum. Hence we conclude that a single decision tree perform better with a smaller complexity penalty.

tree_spec <- decision_tree() %>%
  set_engine("rpart")
class_tree_spec <- tree_spec %>%
  set_mode("classification")
class_tree_wf <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(class_tree_spec %>% set_args(cost_complexity = tune())) %>%
  add_recipe(Pokemon_receipt)

param_grid <- grid_regular(cost_complexity(range = c(-3, -1)), levels = 10)

tune_res <- tune_grid(
  class_tree_wf, 
  resamples = Pokemon_folds, 
  grid = param_grid, 
  metrics = metric_set(roc_auc)
)

autoplot(tune_res)

Exercise 11

abalone_data = read.csv("C:/Users/a1053/Desktop/PSTAT 231/homework-6/data/abalone.csv")

abalone_data <- abalone_data %>%
  mutate(age = rings + 1.5)
set.seed(3435)
Age_split = initial_split(abalone_data, prop=0.8, strata = age)
Age_train = training(Age_split)
Age_test = testing(Age_split)
Age_train = Age_train %>%
  select(-rings)

Age_recipe = recipe(age ~ ., data = Age_train) %>%
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
  step_interact(~type_I:shucked_weight) %>%
  step_interact(~type_M:shucked_weight) %>%
  step_interact(~longest_shell:diameter)%>%
  step_interact(~shucked_weight:shell_weight) %>%
  step_center(all_predictors())%>%
  step_scale(all_predictors())

abalone_folds = vfold_cv(Age_train,v=5,strata = age)

forest_spec <- rand_forest(mtry = tune(),trees = tune(),min_n=tune()) %>%
  set_engine("randomForest",importance = TRUE) %>%
  set_mode("regression")

grid = grid_regular(mtry(range=c(1,8)),trees(range = c(10,1000)),min_n(range = c(5,6)),levels=2)

Abalone_workflow = workflow()%>%
  add_recipe(Age_recipe)%>%
  add_model(forest_spec)

tune_res = tune_grid(
  Abalone_workflow,
  resamples = abalone_folds,
  grid = grid,
  metrics = metric_set(rmse)
)

collect_metrics(tune_res)%>%
  arrange(mean)
